**Rotated Sorted Array Search**

we have a sorted array and it is rotated by a some factor (say k)

[1,2,3,4,5,6,7]   if rotated by  k=3 it becomes  [4,5,6,7,1,2,3]

we have given a **target** value if it is present in our array or not ,

if we have the target value in our array then we have to return **index** 

at which target is present ,if not we simply return -1.

__________________________________________________________________-

Let's start from the most naive approach and gradually progress towards the optimal approach.

as our problem is about searching so first thing came into mind is **LINEAR SEARCH.**

**Approach 1: Linear Search**

we can simply traverse on our array and compare each element of our array one by one with the target value and decide our result on the basis of is **current value of array is equals to target or not .
**
DRY RUN :

nums: [4,5,6,7,1,2,3]     target=2

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7748e614-385f-4a81-8b6e-0de9a2dc101e_1631302063.761646.png)


```cpp

int search(vector<int> nums, int target)
{
	int n = nums.size();

	for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
	{
		int currElement = nums[i];
		if (currElement == target)
		{
			return i;
		}
	}

	return -1;   // if target is not present 
}
```

Time Complexity: O(N)

Space Complexity: O(1)

**Approach 2:  Binary Search:**

As our array is sorted then we can think of binary search.

We apply a modified version of binary search here.

**Algorithm :**

1. If nums[mid]==target then we got the result!
2. if not .. then we can observe that

           one of the left or right subarray about mid is always sorted.

   2.1:  If the left part of mid is sorted  i.e(nums[start] ≤nums[mid])

            a: now we check is our target value falls in the left range then we move our 

              End pointer to mid-1 , by doing this we reduce half of search space in one go.

            b: if target does not fall into left range then we check into right part.

   2.2    if the right part of mid is sorted i.e,(nums[mid]≤nums[end])

            a: we check target value falls into right range then we start pointer to mid+1,

            b: else we move to left part

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/63a590ff-ddee-43f3-8a42-6362f1a7bb1c_1631302089.6877496.png)

