# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
in question, it is given we have to solve it in lon n times. which means we have to use divide and conquer technique.
    if in question complexity is not mentioned , then it is obvious since array is rotated and sorted that is both parts are sorted. we have to eliminate one part so that we can search in right part.

# WHAT IS PIVOT OF AN ROTATED SORTED ARRAY.
It is the index of the array at which array get sorted in two halves. example- [4,5,6,7,8]->[8,4,5,6,7], pivot is 4
# WHY PIVOT????
 we are finding pivot so that we can eliminate the second half and apply search in the correct part.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. firstly we have to find pivot using binary search.
2. then we have to check whether target is less or greater than pivot.
3. if target is greater than pivot apply search on right half else left half.  [4,5,6,7,8]->[8,4,5,6,7] , target is 6.... search is done on [4,5,6,7]
4 apply binary search on the half.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(lon n)

- Space complexity:
