The rotated array can be thought as a composition of two arrays as the picture below shows. We first selected the middle element  and we have to figure in which part of the array we are in. If the nums[mid]>=nums[start], then we are in the red part. If not, we are in the blue part. 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/999f2060-2765-4281-88a5-9fe39777e929_1630004936.2318954.png)

If we are in the red zone we know that the elements in the range [start, mid] are bounded below by nums[start] and are bounded above by nums[mid]. If target is in this range, then it must be located between start and mid so we update the end pointer to point to mid-1. If it is not within this range, then we can disregard every element in the range [start, mid] and we can update the start pointer to point to mid+1. A similar argument works if we happen to be in the blue zone. 

