solutions.content:
* We can have 2 halves (low to mid & mid to high) of Array if we divided b/w Middle.

* We need to check in which side Target can present **But But** we can't check directly by comparing with nums[mid] & Target.

* So, We first check which side is Sorted(one of them will sorted) 
* So,That we can check whether the target lies within that range. If Not, Move to other side of SubArray.


```
int search(vector<int>& nums, int t) {
        int n=nums.size();

        int l=0,h=n-1;

        while(l<=h){
            int mid=(l+h)/2;
            //check mid==t
            if(nums[mid]==t) return mid;

            //check whether left subarray is sorted
            else if(nums[l]<=nums[mid]){
                //if Yes, check whether Target lies b/w this Range else move to right SubArray
                if(t>=nums[l] && t<=nums[mid]){
                    h=mid-1;
                }else{
                    l=mid+1;
                }
            }

            //same for right array
            else{
                if(t>=nums[mid] && t<=nums[h]){
                    l=mid+1;
                }else{
                    h=mid-1;
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
