This occurs because the array is only of length 2, and the element at the `start` and `mid` index is larger than the element at the `end` index. Your code, however, expects that for the first part of the array (`nums[start]` to `nums[mid]`), it will be in sorted order. But due to the pivot at index 0, this is not the case.

To fix this, you can include a check for when `start` and `mid` are equal:

```cpp
