Maintain a map of nodes `Node[] nodes = new Node[101]` where `nodes[i]` will refer to the `ith` node. Use DFS to explore the original graph. As we encounter each node in the original graph, we need to check the `nodes` map first to see if an object has already been created for it. If not we should create it first and then continue exploring all other nodes using DFS.

